com.qtplaf.library.trading.data

Class Data

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qtplaf.library.trading.data.Data

  • public class Data
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class of timed data. An arbitrary number of double values with the starting time. It can be an data (open, high, low, close, volume) pack or the list of values of an indicator.
    Author:
    Miquel Sas

      • valid

        private boolean valid
        A boolean that indicates if the data is valid and, for instance, should be plotted. Recall that some indicators can need a look backward or necessary number of bars to be calculated, and sometimes also a look forward, while the list of data has the same number of elements that the origin instrument list.
